        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <h3>Strong passwords are not enough</h3>
        <p>Passwords are not as secure as we think. There have been numerous password leaks in the last year and it is just a matter of time before they become completely obsolete. A long and complex password won't save users from cyberattacks.</p>
        <h3>One Tok3n for all your apps</h3>
        <p>Two-factor authentication has been used by banks, high corporate, government and health sector for many years now, but hardware and virtual tokens are costly and difficult to integrate. Tok3n is an affordable and easy to integrate two-step-authorization for applications. A modest web service would face major challenges to implement these kind of solutions, like providing alternative account recovery via SMS and phone calls, besides integrating with Google authenticator or developing your own application for all major mobile platforms.</p>
        <p>Once enabled, after the regular user-password authentication (or any other action) provided by your app, the user will be asked to enter the code in the Tok3n app on their smartphones. Tok3n plans to provide easy to implement classes in Ruby, Python, Node.js, PHP, Java, .Net and all your favorite server platforms.</p><p>Tok3n is not only an API. Users can recover their account on our webapp and manage their devices and authorized applications in a secure and easy way. Restful API, can be integrated with your application seamlessly without worrying about account recovery and extra hassle. If the user loses their authorized devices, they still access their account with other authorized device, backup codes or with landline recovery in our users web section.</p>
